ADDITIONAL PERMISSION: PLUGIN AND THEME EXCEPTION
================================================================================

As a special exception under section 7 of the GNU General Public License
version 3, you are granted additional permission to create, distribute, and
license plugins and themes for Luducat under any Open Source Initiative (OSI)
approved license of your choice (see https://opensource.org/licenses),
provided that:

1. The plugin or theme interfaces with Luducat solely through:
   - The documented plugin API (luducat.plugins.base)
   - The theme/stylesheet system
   - Standard inter-process communication

2. The plugin or theme does not contain modified copies of Luducat's
   core source code.

3. The plugin or theme is distributed separately from Luducat, not as
   part of the main application bundle (distribution alongside is permitted).

This exception explicitly permits plugins and themes to use permissive
licenses (MIT, BSD, Apache 2.0, etc.) or other copyleft licenses without
requiring them to be licensed under GPL v3.

This exception does NOT apply to:
- Modifications to Luducat's core application code (GPL v3 applies)
- Forks or derivative versions of Luducat itself (GPL v3 applies)
- Plugins that embed or statically link Luducat source code

